                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="allianceparty_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a political party formed in Northern Ireland in 1970 by people who disagreed with the extreme views of both Catholics and Protestants. The party's original aim was to end the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-troubles" title="Troubles definition"><span class="ndv">Troubles</span></a> by bringing together the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/moderate_1" title="moderate definition"><span class="ndv">moderate</span></a> people from both sides. Now one of its main aims is to support <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/diversity" title="diversity definition"><span class="ndv">diversity</span></a> <span class="gloss" hclass="gloss" htag="span">(= including a wider range of types of people)</span> in Northern Ireland.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
